The paper discusses the Backpropagation algorithm, which is commonly used in neural networks, and its biological plausibility. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the approximation of gradients, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of neural networks and the discussion of biological plausibility also suggest the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of deep feedforward networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV).
